channel.title: Mopar on Wikipedia. o.O
channel.description:
Hello, I was bored today and I found something interesting on Wikipedia.
[edit] Runescape Private Servers For Long RuneScape has been a leading MMORPG in the world of gaming. For the past year or so people have found a way to crack the runescape client (the program that connects to the game server). These versions of the game are not exactly like runescape but are identical in many ways. They share the exact same game engine and map. They also share the same NPCs (Non-Player Characters e.g. Goblins and Demons) and Objects. The only difference the server-side things such as what happens when you click a certain button. Some examples of this is that on a base private server you will not have quests and so forth. You will also not have registering accounts through the internet. To create an account on a private server you must type in the username and passwords in the appropriate boxes in the modified client. This client can be obtained at http://www.moparisthebest.com/moparscape.html. Servers are connected to through ip addresses. The first person to discover servers and edited the client goes by the name WinterLove. The First public server ever was Blakescape. The best servers of all time are WhiteScape, Testscape, Hybridscape and Avatar. Those servers got the closest to being like RuneScape by making quests, full magic, full of all statistics. The owner of those servers were WhiteFang, Nvi ible, Miss Silabsoft and Phate. Whitescape 3.2 was one of the major revolutions in private servers. Since it was the first server to have working shops. This server was coded by whitefang
Hybridscape was one of the best releases to evolve private servers since it features never before seen updates such as server console. However the server that took the people's hearts is called cheezscape made by xerozcheez. Cheezscape has had 4 releases: Cheezscape update 63, Cheezscape update 78, Cheezscape 80, and Cheezscape u12.
Phate also known as StAnger was the owner of Avatorium and RuneStatus. Phate has released Avatar one of the most powerful Private servers today.
KAITNEIKS:
Kaitneiks was one of the most dominate forums on Runescape Private Servers. The website was called after its owner Kaitneik. The forum also featured a lot of runescape exploits and cheating. The community released many great cheats such as the great autorune, aryan cheating client, SCAR and many more .Kaineiks had alot of expert coders. Kaitnieks had simply shutdown the site because he wanted to get on with his life. Later that year he became a father.
Moparisthebest:
Moparisthebest was a new re-birth of kaitnieks. It still has many veterans from the older days and it continues to strive higher. The cheating has slowed down but the community is still flowing and it is continually growing,
Rs-Server:
This forum was known for its wars against Avatarorim, RuneStatus and Rage-zone. This forum was nearly a rebirth of Kaitneiks. Many veteran coders came there people such as Fasga, MrWicked, Miss Silabsoft, Xerozcheez, Wolf, Santa Clause, Tasty noob, Ramenryoko, Drunkenolma, Gander, rsrules, rat dawg, swift,callmedude, kevin and many more are from. In January 2007 rs-server got split up since Kevin got greedy and banned the Owner of rs-server (Gander) and screwed him over, all the veteran coders left since gander got banned and the site had been getting hacked by Gander and Xerozcheez ever since the. Rs-server went independent and re-named itself Rune-Server. And Gander made his own new site called RuneSoft these two sites have been rivals ever since.
Xerozcheez:
Since Xerozcheez has left rs-server, he has moved onto his own Java codes. The more famous code he designed was the 'Firefox Password Stealer' which was implemented into many of his codes released on the Internet. When opened, the application would scan for Firefox and steal the file which contained saved passwords it would then send it to Xerozcheez resulting in him being able to use your saved passwords as his own.
Please take the time to read it.
The link I found this on was http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Articles_for_creation/2006-06-21
I found it kinda' interesting.
Oh well, I'll try and find more interesting articles. :P
~ x0
